  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ gas 9, then add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 175ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619018132487-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619018132487-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619018132487-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619018132487-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619018132487-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Cut 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Cut 2 long rectangles of <strong>tin foil</strong> (approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper), overlap the foil and place on a baking tray (cooking for 4 or more? Do this twice!)</p><p>Tip: Overlapping the foil ensures that the fish is completely encased for cooking</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> in the centre of the doubled foil</p><p>Scatter with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and dot the <strong>butter</strong> evenly over</p><p>Drizzle your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> evenly over the basa</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/746.-step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Scrunch the edges of the foil together around the fish to form a sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>baked basa with soy honey butter</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
